Sentencas: The interfacial resistance of Ni-Y2O2-stabilized ZrO2 (Ni-YSZ) anodes on YSZ electrolytes has been reduced by inserting thin interfacial layers of TiO2-doped YSZ (YZT) or Y2O3-doped CeO2 (YDC).
Titulo: Effect of mixed-conducting interfacial layers on solid oxide fuel cell anode performance

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy measurements at temperatures ranging from 600 to 750 degrees C typically showed a high frequency are (HFA) and a low frequency are (LFA).
Titulo: Effect of mixed-conducting interfacial layers on solid oxide fuel cell anode performance

Sentencas: The HFA was reduced by the addition of either interlayer, with a larger reduction for YDC.
Titulo: Effect of mixed-conducting interfacial layers on solid oxide fuel cell anode performance

Sentencas: This presumably resulted from enhanced charge transfer due to the mixed conductivity and/or enhanced redox reaction rate of the interfacial layer.
Titulo: Effect of mixed-conducting interfacial layers on solid oxide fuel cell anode performance

Sentencas: The LFA, which was apparently related to mass-transport processes, grew with decreasing YSZ surface roughness and increasing interlayer thickness.
Titulo: Effect of mixed-conducting interfacial layers on solid oxide fuel cell anode performance

Sentencas: The overall interfacial resistance was minimized for layer thicknesses of -0.5 mu m.
Titulo: Effect of mixed-conducting interfacial layers on solid oxide fuel cell anode performance

Sentencas: The lowest interfacial resistances in 97% H-2 + H2O, 0.13 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C, and 0.29 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C, were obtained with 0.5 mu m thick YDC interfacial layers.
Titulo: Effect of mixed-conducting interfacial layers on solid oxide fuel cell anode performance
